  "title": "Technical Security Consultant (Post-Sales)",
  "description": "<p>As a <strong>Technical Security Consultant (Post-Sales)</strong>, you’ll be responsible for deploying, supporting, and troubleshooting network security solutions for enterprise customers and channel partners. You will ensure customer success by providing exceptional technical implementation and escalation support.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>✅ <strong>Key Responsibilities:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Implement, configure, and maintain network security solutions across on-premise and cloud environments.</li>\n  <li>Provide Level 2/3 technical support, troubleshoot complex incidents, and perform root cause analysis.</li>\n  <li>Conduct technical workshops, knowledge transfers, and handovers to clients and partners.</li>\n  <li>Collaborate with vendors and internal teams for escalated issue resolution.</li>\n  <li>Monitor system performance to ensure reliability, scalability, and security compliance.</li>\n  <li>Support upgrade, patching, and lifecycle management activities.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>🎯 <strong>Requirements:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>2–5 years of experience in <strong>pre-sales or post-sales engineering</strong> for <strong>leading or emerging cybersecurity products</strong>.</li>\n  <li>Strong understanding of <strong>network security technologies</strong>, including <strong>firewalls, VPNs, IDS/IPS, endpoint protection, and threat intelligence platforms</strong>.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>✨ We appreciate every application, but only shortlisted candidates will be contacted. Thank you for your understanding!</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>WeCruit Pte Ltd | EA License No. 20C0270</strong><br>\n <strong>EA Personnel:</strong> Tan Soon Hock (Steven) | <strong>Registration No.:</strong> R1109889</p>",
